-- LSE appoints new head of primary markets
-- By Clare Hutchison
-- Mon Jun 02, 2014 07:46AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, June 2 (Reuters) - London Stock Exchange Group <LSE.L> said on Monday it has appointed former Espirito Santo <BES.LS> investment banker John Millar as head of primary markets.

Millar will focus on generating initial public offerings and will report to Raffaele Jerusalmi, LSE's director of capital markets and the chief executive of Borsa Italiana, and London Stock Exchange CEO Alexander Justham, the group said in a statement.